          },
          "helpfulVotes": "11 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Hydrating skin tint!",
          "reviewText": "I really like this skin tint. It\u2019s hydrating, has light coverage with a dewy finish, and looks very natural on the skin. The texture out of the tube is creamy, then thins out when you apply to the skin. It blends easily, and lasts well with minimal fading throughout my normal work day. I have enjoyed almost every foundation product I\u2019ve tried from No 7 brand, and this one is great for everyday wear.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2025",
          "customer": "S Pross",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AE4OTLYOKJ634VVQMJBUOBNHAIVA",
          "customerStarsRating": 4,
          "productSpecs": {
            "size": "1 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)",
            "color": "01 - Fair"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "12 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "My experience as a woman turning 75 in two months",
          "reviewText": "I am lucky in that genetically and with a few inexpensive products I don't have a lot of wrinkles on my face. HOWEVER while I'm not splotchy, I don't have as even a tone to my skin and I wanted something light to just make it look, well, BETTER. At my age, I find things like putty, spackle (still can't believe they call some beauty products this), primer, don't really seem to help. I just wanted something to smooth out my skin a bit. I have tried foundations supposedly MEANT for MATURE skin. I found most of them oxidize (I'm very pale), so when I remove them, the cloth is ORANGE. I looked at reviews of at least a dozen BB creams, CC creams, and then found this tinted moisturizer. EUREKA! FOR ME this works GREAT. PROS: Coverage - LIGHT, but I can layer a bit by gently rubbing in a first coat, and just blotting on second coat. STILL really light but a bit more coverage. LOOK - It looks like my skin, but just better. AND it doesn't oxidize meaning when I remove it, same color as when I put it on. BLENDS - easy to blend. I often put first coat on with fingers, second coat I blot on with little sponge and takes minutes for it to dry. COLOR - After years, I found something that is the color of my skin and is so natural looking. TEXTURE - LIGHT, not like slathering on a full foundation. PRICE - Not rich, do not spend a fortune on face products. THIS is well worth it. I don't wear it every day if I'm just around the house, but when I go out. ONE CAVEAT - CAREFUL squeezing it. Quite a bit comes out at once. BOTTOMLINE: THRILLED to have found this at almost 75! It was the ONE thing I was missing in my minimal face makeup routine!",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2025",
          "customer": "pleinelune",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEQITYPQMHYKRIGZBQFPDKGTAJGQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "size": "1 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)",
            "color": "01 - Fair"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "52 people found this helpful"
